Located at the intersection of north China's Shanxi Province and northwest China's Shaanxi Province, Hukou Waterfall is the only yellow waterfall in the world and the second largest waterfall in China after Huangguoshu in Guizhou Province. The Colors of Nature This series combines music, color and natural scenery to give viewers a sensory experience. For more: Snowy Kanas in NW China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region The beauty of yellow sand The beauty of the color black The beauty of the color brown Do you like the color green? The beauty of yellow leaves The Colors of Nature: Pink peach flowers in Tibet (Cover images via CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)